Global Funds Buy Net 24.4 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-10-10T03:31:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/global-funds-buy-net-24-4-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors bought a net 24.4
billion rupees ($496 million) of Indian equity  derivatives  on
Oct. 7, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 3.5 percent to 823 billion rupees, or 38.5
percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees last year on Sept. 21, 2010.  Foreign funds bought a net 4.92 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment on Oct. 7, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
